transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hey, John. This is Jeannie Johnson. My husband's right here, Greg Johnson.

Speaker 1: We were calling in regards to his recent order and just want to make sure that he's not on an auto trip.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Let's talk to you.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay. Thank you for calling us back. Can I get your date of birth?

Speaker 2: 2-11-66.

Speaker 1: He's been having a lot of trouble in the bedroom.

Speaker 2: You're in Portageville, Missouri?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay. And you don't want to receive future orders, right?

Speaker 1: Excuse me?

Speaker 2: We don't want to be on an auto trip.

Speaker 1: Okay. Yeah. I'll make sure that, yeah, that's fine. So I'll make sure that's the case for you. That's not a problem.

Speaker 2: Yeah. And another thing, you know, like on where they're advertising this at?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: They're advertising this as a totally new medication. Got a different picture of it and everything on there.

Speaker 1: Like it says it works in 11 minutes and lasts for so long.

Speaker 2: This is the totally same pill that I got two years ago because I got the bottle and some of them in it right now.

Speaker 1: Well, sir, so if that happened, we need to fix it because we do sell both kinds.

Speaker 2: So there may have been a mix-up at the pharmacy when they filled it.

Speaker 1: So your current one that you got from us is the same as you've gotten before?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: And the pills are identical and everything?

Speaker 2: Exactly. Same numbers and everything on them.

Speaker 1: Does it say AC-340 on the pill?

Speaker 2: What did you say now?

Speaker 1: AC-340. Is that what it says on the pill?

Speaker 2: I don't know. I think it was just – yeah, the new ones are right there somewhere where you're at.

Speaker 1: The older ones are right here.

Speaker 2: So the ones we sent you, though, if you could grab those ones and just confirm real quick.

Speaker 1: Because if we screwed up, I'm just going to fix it.

Speaker 2: I understand the ownership. I'm not talking about that part, but I do want to get you the right one.

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: Yeah, this is them right here.

Speaker 1: You found those too, but here's the AC-340 one on work.

Speaker 2: Don't get them mixed up. You're wanting the wrong bottle. You're going to have to read this.

Speaker 1: AC-340.

Speaker 2: AC-340.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, so that was the wrong one.

Speaker 2: So yours should have just said 100 on the pill.

Speaker 1: So the fact it doesn't say just 100 obviously confirms it's wrong.

Speaker 2: So I'll get you the right one, sir.

Speaker 1: Again, I understand the shipment stuff, but I will get you the right pills.

Speaker 2: Okay. You have any idea when they're going to ship out?

Speaker 1: It should ship out tomorrow.

Speaker 2: I'm putting it through right now.

Speaker 1: It's going to go through as a $0 transaction on your account, like your score blue account.

Speaker 2: I'm doing it that way just so you get email updates with shipping and stuff.

Speaker 1: Right. All right, man. Well, I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, because these are exactly the same.

Speaker 1: We were expecting something totally the same because it was a totally different picture,

Speaker 2: and they're supposed to do so good.

Speaker 1: I totally understand. I'm sorry about the mistake.

Speaker 2: Just so you know, though, they are going to still be a white diamond pill,

Speaker 1: but if it says 100, the chemical makeup of that pill is better and different,

Speaker 2: and it will work better.

Speaker 1: If you're not happy with it, though, after you try the ones I'm resending out,

Speaker 2: call us back, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, man. I certainly appreciate you.

Speaker 2: And still, either way, there's not going to be any future auto-ship.

Speaker 1: Right. You're all set there. I'm just getting your mistake.

Speaker 2: The mistake, you're fixed.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right. Well, we sure thank you.

Speaker 1: You're welcome. Have a good one.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
